 debate the analytic arguments but infuse their discussion with their personal experiences, which have shaped their perspectives on multiculturalism in Canada. This volume is a highly personal as well as strongly analytic discussion of multiculturalism in Canada today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCivil rightsxCanada. 0aCivil rightszCanada. 0aDroits de l'hommexCanadaxCanadaxCanada. 0aDroits de l'hommezCanadazCanadazCanada. 0aMulticulturalismxCanada. 0aMulticulturalismzCanada. 0aMulticulturalismexCanada. 0aMulticulturalismezCanada. 4aPolitical Science. 4aSocial Science: Multiculturalism. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aCameron, David Robertson, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCameron, David Robertson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIacobucci, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIbbitson, John, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aIbbitson, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKymlicka, Will, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeisel, John, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMeisel, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSiddiqui, Haroon, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSiddiqui, Haroon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStein, Janice Gross, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aValpy, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aValpy, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Pa